<template><div><p>Both OGP (Open Graph Protocol) and JSON-LD (JavaScript Object Notation for Linked Data) are methods used to add metadata to web pages, but they serve different purposes and are used by different platforms.</p>
<h2 id="open-graph-protocol-ogp" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#open-graph-protocol-ogp"><span>Open Graph Protocol (OGP)</span></a></h2>
<p>OGP was originally developed by Facebook and is widely used by social media platforms (such as Facebook, Twitter, LinkedIn, etc.) to display rich previews when a webpage is shared. By including specific meta tags in the <code v-pre>&lt;head&gt;</code> section of your HTML, you can control the title, description, image, URL, and other details that appear in social media posts.</p>
