<p>JSON-LD is a method for encoding linked data using JSON. It is primarily used to add structured data to web pages so that search engines (like Google) can better understand the content and context of your page. This, in turn, can improve your pageâ€™s appearance in search results, sometimes leading to rich snippets or other enhanced search features.</p>
